modules.description: Provides key exchange and scalar multiplication operations for elliptic curve cryptography using the Curve25519 algorithm. Works with 32-byte private and public keys, and 64-byte shared secrets. Enables secure communication channels by generating shared secrets from public keys and private scalars.

Provides functions to convert between string and integer array representations of cryptographic keys, compute shared secrets using ECDH, and derive public keys from secret keys. Works with private, public, and shared key types represented as 32-byte integer arrays. Computes shared secrets between a secret key and a public key, and allows printing and comparison of key values.
